          <td width="30">&nbsp;</td>
          <td width="405" class="texte">
FULL TIME POSITION, Bordeaux France<BR><BR><BR>Reporting to the Financial Direction, you will assist our Cost Controller. This experience will help you develop your financial skills in a young, international and dynamic environment.<BR><BR>Principle duties and responsibilities<BR> <BR>·	In order to guarantee that we respect our commercial agreements, you will manage the financial relationship with our clients in Europe (telecom operators) by generating and controlling all the invoicing <BR>·	You will manage cash collection <BR>·	You will supervise the payment of royalties to our external partners <BR>·	You will update the financial reporting documents <BR>·	Using our specialised software, you will prepare the analysis of the cost of all projects in progress <BR>·	You will be involved in the everyday activities of our Financial Department (administrative tasks, new projects, etc …).<BR><BR>Education, experience and skills required<BR><BR>·	You have a 2 year diploma/certificate in accountancy, cost control or finance <BR>·	You have between 2-4 years experience in a similar job in either a company  or a consultancy accountancy firm ;<BR>·	Rigorous and methodical,  you are highly reliable in your work <BR>·	Extremely involved in your job, a proactive individual, you regularly propse new solutions in order to improve  our financial processes ;<BR>·	You will manage all external contacts (high level) as well as  internal ones (collection and transmission of financial data), so we will need  someone with excellent people  skills.<BR>·	You are fluent in French and English<BR><BR>If you are flexible, dynamic and you are eager to be a member of a very international team (Dutch, Spanish, Italian, French, Iranian, Chinese…) and contribute to the further <BR>growth of this highly international company (English is the working <BR>language), then please send us your CV.<BR><BR>We feel it is very important to help develop the skills of all our employees.<BR>Thus, in order to help you along your career path, we do our<BR>best to maximize the possibility of internal promotion.<BR><BR><BR><BR>
